name: MajorInjuries
title: Major Injuries
description: This set of ICD-10-CM values contains major injury diagnoses, developed  to be associated with a patient fall.
purpose:
(Clinical Focus: The purpose of this ICD-10-CM value set is to identify major injuries or death that could occur as a result of a fall within a hospital setting.),(Data Element Scope: This value set may use a model element related to Diagnosis.),(Inclusion Criteria: Includes ICD-10-CM concepts that represent major injuries that could occur as a result of a fall within a hospital setting, such as large bone fractures, closed head injuries, and internal bleeding),(Exclusion Criteria: Excludes moderate injuries (such as lacerations, open wounds, dislocations, sprains, and muscle strains.) 
Excludes minor injuries (such as abrasions, small bone fractures.) 
Excludes injuries as a result of a fall that could not occur within a hospital setting)
